## 1️⃣ UserRoleModel

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`userrole` table** in the database.
**Step 1:** The system has different **roles for users**.
**Step 2:** `id` is the **unique id for the role**.
**Step 3:** `name` stores the **role name** (example: admin, user).
**Step 4:** `description` explains **what the role is for**.
**Step 5:** `image` stores an **image related to the role**.
**Step n:** So this table **stores different roles available in the system**.

---

## 2️⃣ UserProfileModel

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`user_profile` table**.
**Step 1:** It stores **extra profile information of users**.
**Step 2:** `id` is the **unique id for the profile record**.
**Step 3:** `userid` links the **profile to a specific user**.
**Step 4:** `gender` stores the **user's gender**.
**Step 5:** `alternatemobile` stores an **additional phone number**.
**Step 6:** `logo` stores the **user profile image or logo**.
**Step n:** So this table **stores additional profile details of users**.

---

## 3️⃣ UserPlan

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`userplan` table**.
**Step 1:** It stores **which subscription plan a user has purchased**.
**Step 2:** `userid` identifies **which user owns the plan**.
**Step 3:** `planid` identifies **which plan the user selected**.
**Step 4:** `paymentReferenceId` stores the **payment transaction reference**.
**Step 5:** `active` tells **whether the plan is currently active**.
**Step 6:** `datecreated` stores **when the plan started**.
**Step 7:** `planExpiryDate` stores **when the plan will expire**.
**Step n:** So this table **tracks user subscriptions and plan status**.

---

## 4️⃣ UserOutcomes

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`user_outcomes` table**.
**Step 1:** It connects **users with outcomes** in the system.
**Step 2:** `id` is the **unique record id**.
**Step 3:** `userid` identifies **which user the record belongs to**.
**Step 4:** `outcomeid` identifies **which outcome is linked to the user**.
**Step n:** So this table **stores outcomes assigned to users**.

---

## 5️⃣ UserOtpModel

**Step 0:** This model represents the **`userotp` table**.
**Step 1:** It stores **OTP (one-time password) details for users**.
**Step 2:** `userid` identifies **which user requested the OTP**.
**Step 3:** `otp` stores the **OTP value**.
**Step 4:** `status` shows **whether the OTP is used or valid**.
**Step 5:** `validity` stores **until when the OTP is valid**.
**Step 6:** `createdtimestamp` stores **when the OTP was created**.
**Step n:** So this table **manages OTP verification for users**.
